---
const tools = ['GA4', 'GTM', 'BigQuery', 'Looker Studio', 'Meta CAPI', 'Google Ads', 'Shopify', 'OneTrust'];
---

<section id="about" class="relative py-20 md:py-28">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-5 lg:px-8">
    <div class="grid gap-10 md:grid-cols-[0.9fr_1.1fr] md:items-center">
      <div class="reveal soft-panel p-7 md:p-10">
        <div class="mb-8 flex items-center gap-4">
          <div class="flex h-16 w-16 items-center justify-center rounded-3xl bg-navy font-display text-2xl font-extrabold text-white">AR</div>
          <div>
            <p class="font-display text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-[-0.045em] text-navy">Artem Reiter</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-muted">Independent analytics consultant</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <h2 class="mb-5 font-display text-[clamp(2.2rem,4vw,4rem)] font-extrabold leading-[0.98] text-navy">
          Senior specialist energy, not faceless platform energy.
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg leading-8 text-body">
          Reiterweb is built around one practical promise: find what is wrong in the measurement stack, prove it clearly, and make the fix understandable for marketing and engineering.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="reveal reveal-delay-1">
        <p class="kicker mb-4">What this replaces</p>
        <h3 class="mb-6 font-display text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-[-0.05em] text-navy">No more “the dashboard says so”.</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          {[
            'Every material finding should have evidence: screenshot, payload, query, DebugView or report comparison.',
            'Every fix should have a business reason: inflated ROAS, missing signal, broken consent, wrong dashboard logic.',
            'Every recommendation should be implementable: owner, priority, dependency and retest path.',
          ].map((line) => (
            <div class="card flex gap-4 p-5">
              <span class="mt-2 h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-teal"></span>
              <p class="leading-7 text-body">{line}</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
        <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
          {tools.map((tool) => (
            <span class="rounded-full border border-line bg-white px-3 py-1.5 font-mono text-[11px] text-muted">{tool}</span>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
